text: I’m disabling ads ;(
too many malicious ads pushing through even with me yelling at the ad network
Kill them all'
i might be hitting up you guys for ideas on alternative forms of monetization
premium features or something like that people would be voluntarily willing to pay, some shit like patreon etc
im going too look into more trustworthy ad networks as well
either way i can’t survive on just cardkingdom at this point
Just pull a Pucatrade, run a kickstarter, promise new features and then don't follow through on any of them. Minus the "fade into irrelevance" part that is.
Pretty sure those two things go hand in hand
True story
I struggle wrapping my head around patreon for websites. Scryfall is planning it but i just dont understand the perks people would care about
What are some ideas that you DON'T want to do? Maybe help narrow down what options before we get started
Well some things: im not worried about one time cash investments
Like for example kickstarter is unnecessary. If i can solve my problems and have sustainable revenue just by having a chunk of cash i can do that myself
Patreon is nice because its recurring revenue

What about a premium subscription type membership? Create login's for people, then you can use the funds from that to fund a deckbuilder as the key feature along with whatever else people would look for. Message boards maybe? Though with Reddit/Salvation etc I think that medium is pretty crowded already
Adding user accounts to the website is the prerequisite for a number of ideas that revolve around premium accounts. Which is no small deat
Feat
Yea, I assumed as much
Ive wanted to do it a long time though
What features would make you want to spend $3/mo?
Being able to build my deck right on the site and have access to the recs and statistical breakdown right while I'm building.
Man id want to make that a nonpaid feature though
Some sort of live ticker for your deck, if you add/take out any given card it shows you what the color spread does, the average deck curve etc
Yeah the deckbuilder is on my list of ideas
But i duno if i want to charg efor it
One idea i had is premium users could have beta access to new features for a month or some shit
But then that puts me on the hook to actually do shit
What about some way to "favorite" cards or dog ear them for users to revisit later?
Yeah thats a good one. We could send out notifications with new sets coming out....
I guess my hangup is i dont know if i want to paywall out features that would have general appeal
Sure
What is something you wish we had that nobody else has?
Advanced features thst only a subpopulation would use id be more inclined, or some sort of incentive like removing ads (though i cant do that now lol)
Add a slack channel for users where they can talk to us?
Yea that was another thought of mine, a feature to have ads disabled if you pay $X
It works for BSB
I think a different ad network would be a better option.
Whatever that is.
Pay to have a writer breakdown your deck and do a Deck Doctor type article on it?
I'm trying to think of premium accounts but I don't know that it would bring in the revenue.
No.
Oh God no.
You have no idea how inundated we would be. And a proper deck doctor is a lot of work
So to be clear i am looking into new ad networks, but the whole thing is very irritating
If they pay us for it though?
That should deter the broad masses sufficiently
For that kind of money we could devote a whole podcast to the deck. If we ever get the podcast together that is.
Anyone buy anything magic related on amazon?
I buy sleeves
KMC perfect fits
My store rarely has them in stock, and you can get like 500 on Amazon for 12 bucks or something
Same as <@U4V5EHQ2G> I ordered a lot of perfect fits recently.
I don't even bother taking them off cards anymore, I just leave them on everything, and I slap them on any semi-valuable card in a binder
Same here. To both buying and usage
Moved away from KMC. Quality became crap.
I switched from kmc to dragon shields a year ago or s
Very good
I still have some old KMCs unused, but I’m transitioning to dragon shields also
I did have a stack of KMC hyper matte's but since I started actually putting the decks together that I write about for the most part it's eaten through my supply
I've never liked dragon shields, I'm hoping these ultra pro eclipses are as good as folks have been raving about
Ive never had a dragon shield split
However the fronts do get “foggy” and my foils arent as sparkly
The part that I didn't like was how long they were and the tops got super crinkled
Oh you mean the inner sleeve. Yes I’m still using those.
Yeah, outer sleeves I use the Dragonshield Mattes
Supposedly Dragonshield makes an inner now too, but I have so many of the KMC perfect fits there's no need to change
Matt, I haven't had the crinkle issue with more recent Dragonshields
Are they still super long on the part beyond where the card ends?
I actually found some of the Dragonshield inner selves and they’re good.
Not super long, no
fuck, I'd deck doctor for 100 bucks
But I also bought about 3k of perfect fits because I’m obsessive with double sleeving.
Well, that revenue would go to the site to make up for the ad revenue it isn't getting anymore.
Though, if we got some kind of DD commission, then, yeah, sign me up.
the list of things I've done for 20 bucks is pretty high, so anything north of that is gravy
not as high as someone who used to be addicted to meth, but still
<https://youtu.be/rDOL4syH4T0?t=5m16s>
